WEBVTT

00:02.326 --> 00:03.401
What is this?

00:04.513 --> 00:05.706
It is a crayon.

00:06.153 --> 00:07.647
I use it for coloring.

00:08.243 --> 00:09.049
What is that?

00:10.235 --> 00:11.231
It is a pot.

00:11.905 --> 00:13.489
We use it to cook.

00:14.604 --> 00:16.561
What do you use to write?

00:17.415 --> 00:19.151
Here is a pencil.

00:19.883 --> 00:21.999
I use a pencil to write.

00:22.973 --> 00:25.493
Here are a knife and scissors.

00:26.070 --> 00:28.590
Do you use a knife for cutting paper?

00:29.677 --> 00:33.277
No, I use scissors for cutting paper.

00:40.122 --> 00:43.466
What, what, what, what do you see?

00:44.005 --> 00:47.361
Hammer, hammer, hammer, here is a hammer.

00:47.757 --> 00:51.104
What, what, what, for what do you use it?

00:51.480 --> 00:54.737
Pound, pound, pound, I use it for pounding.

00:55.258 --> 00:58.485
What, what, what, what do you see?

00:58.891 --> 01:02.356
Shovel, shovel, shovel, here is a shovel.

01:02.777 --> 01:05.988
What, what, what, for what do you use it?

01:06.487 --> 01:09.883
Dig, dig, dig, I use it for digging.

